article.description: — Isiah Kirby recorded 17 points and 11 rebounds to lead Southeastern Louisiana to a 69-57 win over Central Arkansas on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Kirby lifts SE Louisiana past Central Arkansas 69-57
article.linkText: Kirby lifts SE Louisiana past Central Arkansas 69-57
article.story: HAMMOND, La. -- — Isiah Kirby recorded 17 points and 11 rebounds to lead Southeastern Louisiana to a 69-57 win over Central Arkansas on Wednesday night. Keon Clergeot had 15 points for Southeastern Louisiana (5-11, 3-4 Southland Conference). Joe Kasperzyk added 13 points. Gus Okafor had 10 points. Rylan Bergersen had 13 points and six assists for the Bears (3-12, 2-5), who have now lost five games in a row. Collin Cooper added 10 points. SK Shittu had 10 rebounds. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
